      {
        "id": "eisiYv8HgxdYoAdd",
        "title": "Text 4",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Next, we want to be able to annotate the seismic signals you see. To do this, </p><ul><li>Drag or click to place the &quot;Data Cards&quot; tile above. </li><li>Take a screenshot of one of the signals in the Raspberry Shake data. </li><li>Put your cursor in the Waveform row, then paste your screenshot using Ctrl-V.  </li><li>Update your description based on the image (station, dates and time). </li><li>Make new cards with new waveforms. You can also paste waveform screenshots into sketch tiles and draw on them to point out features.</li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      }
